@ccheong @Kelly Weldon @edbyford @pulkitc @rfreixa @marco_n @edbyford Hi folks (I have probably missed few relevant people) - Regarding the fleet management design . I have watched the meeting video and I have few inputs:
  1. I agree that in general AWS is the model to follow
  2. We heard from AWS enterprise users that what they are missing there is more fine grained utilisation metrics: they need them for chargeback and for capacity planning. They also needed more metrics then cloudwatch provided to understand where an application flow faced / created a bottleneck
  3. From our community user experience so far with monitoring clusters on K8s - users need some operator generated metadata sent with the metrics so it is easier for them to associate data service node or object metrics with the application
  4. The locations of the clusters are very important (in terms of metadata signifying AZs and Regions as well as region geography or country) because apps deployments are: 1. need to meet H/A defence lines which are an app concern and not infra concern and 2. apps need to meet data regulation concerns
  5. I’m still confuse about the GUI / CLI responsibilities in different sale scenarios: In SaaS scenario it seems natural to me that the user can easily navigate from Tanzu console to fleet management and not use another tool. In the case of on-prem: I assume some customers will buy a specific service rather than the whole suite. will they still have to use TSM or DSM?

Data Management for VMware Tanzu v1.0 is live on Tanzu Net!
Customers can now run their own database “as a service” on vSphere for their whole organization to simplify, automate, and easily scale database provisioning and management. This release includes the following features:
  • Data services integrated include multiple versions of Postgres and MySQL v8
  • Fully automated provisioning, backups, database engine updates and security patching
  • Single node and HA deployment of database instances in just a few clicks
  • Data in transit secured with TLS
  • Restore and point-in-time restore from backups to recover from failure
  • Restrict instance creation to predefined t-shirt sizes and scale anytime as necessary
  • Monitor database health with metrics on resource utilization, database activity and usage
  • Supported platforms include vSphere 6.7 and 7
Please see the release notes for more details, download the product from Tanzu Net and try it out on your vSphere infrastructure. We look forward to your feedback. You can reply to this message or reach us on dms-pm@vmware.com.

@Cooper90s a side-note on Tanzu Data Services Pack from Tanzu Data Services PnP FAQ:
Tanzu Data Services Pack includes 30 Cores of Tanzu RabbitMQ, 24 cores of Tanzu SQL and 12 cores of Tanzu GemFire. Restricted to 1 quantity per customer. This is not a mix and match, it is for this specific count of Cores for each product. While this "Pack" is available, it is only intended as a Tanzu Data Services introduction offering. The TDS products should be sold individually when a customer needs more than what is available in the single qty of the Tanzu Data Services "Pack".  If the customer is interested on Postgres only, it would be beneficial to use the Tanzu SQL SKU instead.

@Cooper90s a side-note on Tanzu Data Services Pack from Tanzu Data Services PnP FAQ:
Tanzu Data Services Pack includes 30 Cores of Tanzu RabbitMQ, 24 cores of Tanzu SQL and 12 cores of Tanzu GemFire. Restricted to 1 quantity per customer. This is not a mix and match, it is for this specific count of Cores for each product. While this "Pack" is available, it is only intended as a Tanzu Data Services introduction offering. The TDS products should be sold individually when a customer needs more than what is available in the single qty of the Tanzu Data Services "Pack".  If the customer is interested on Postgres only, it would be beneficial to use the Tanzu SQL SKU instead.

VMware SQL with Postgres for Kubernetes - What's New | VMware
VMware SQL with Postgres for Kubernetes (VMware SQL with Postgres) is a relational database-as-a-service that automates the installation, management, monitoring, and updating of containerized Postgres instances running on-premises or in any cloud. In the past few VMware SQL with Postgres releases, the focus was on improving the availability and recoverability of the managed instances. Version 1.9 is highlighted by two features that enhance the manageability of Postgres instances and the deployment flexibility of the VMware SQL with Postgres product.

Hey All, VMware GemFire for Tanzu Application Service 1.14.9 is live on Tanzu Net! I am pleased to thank the GemFire Tile and docs teams for their hard work.
Please see the Release Notes for more details about the release. Please try it, and share your feedback with me or in this channel #gemfire
Some notable items in this release-
  • Fixed a “Response exceeded maximum allowed length” error that occurred while running the prime-cluster-for-pcc errand by truncating its output.
  • This release supports VMware GemFire for Redis Apps v1.1.0.
  • This release supports VMware Tanzu Application Service for VMs (TAS) versions 2.7, 2.8, 2.9, 2.10, 2.11, 2.12, 2.13 (partial), 3.0, and 4.0.
  • This version of VMware GemFire for Tanzu Application Service runs GemFire 9.15.6.
